  "title": "Chinese Pastor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Faith Assembly</strong></p><p>We're a vibrant multi-generational church that is passionate about manifesting the love and power of Christ in our families, community and nations.  </p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Faith Assembly is seeking a visionary and relational <strong>Assistant Chinese-speaking Pastor </strong>to help lead, disciple, and multiply our vibrant Chinese-speaking community. If you have a passion for spiritual formation and a heart for reaching the lost, we invite you to join our team.</p><p><strong>The Role</strong><br />Your primary mission will be to foster spiritual growth and expand the reach of the Chinese-speaking ministry. You will work closely with church leadership to transition seekers into disciples and members into leaders.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Discipleship & Pastoral Care:</strong> Provide oversight and biblical guidance to members, ensuring they are nurtured and supported in their walk with Christ.</p></li><li><p><strong>Community Outreach:</strong> Strategize and lead initiatives to engage the local Chinese-speaking community and share the Gospel.</p></li><li><p><strong>Leadership Development:</strong> Identify, mentor, and empower emerging leaders to multiply the ministry’s impact.</p></li><li><p><strong>Church-Level Events:</strong> Collaborate on the planning and execution of large-scale church events and ad hoc projects.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Spiritual Maturity: </strong>A personal and growing relationship with God. </li><li><p><strong>Educational Background:</strong> Minimum of a <strong>Bachelor’s Degree in Theology</strong> from a recognized and accredited institution.</p></li><li><p><strong>Character & Fit:</strong> A collaborative <strong>team player</strong> and a growth mindset.<br /></p><p>To apply, email: enquiry@faithag.org.sg</p></li></ul>",
